71922.name: Abyssal Depths
71922.text: Draw your two lowest Cost minions.

72318.name: Abyssal Wave
72318.text: Deal 4 damage to all minions. Give your opponent an Abyssal Curse.
72318.flavorText: Often followed up with a chasmic handshake.

73906.name: Amalgam of the Deep
73906.text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly minion. Discover a minion of the same minion type.
73906.flavorText: Most explorers call it a success to find just one new species. Imagine Finley's excitement when he identified ten at once!

74907.name: Ambassador Faelin
74907.text: Battlecry: Put 3 Colossal minions on the bottom of your deck.
74907.flavorText: For thousands of years, Faelin has longed to return to his homeland. Will Zin-Azshari be as he hopes, or are the secrets of the deep better left forgotten?

72314.name: Anchored Totem
72314.text: After you summon a 1-Cost minion, give it +2/+1.
72314.flavorText: The Naga devised the perfect retaliation to any pirates dropping anchor in their domain: vandalism.

76224.name: Ancient Krakenbane
76224.text: Battlecry: If you've cast three spells while holding this, deal 5 damage. ( left!) (Ready!)

73774.name: Aquatic Form
73774.text: Dredge. If you have the Mana to play the card this turn, draw it.
73774.flavorText: How long can YOU hold your breath underwater?

72657.name: Azsharan Defector
72657.text: Rush. Deathrattle: Put a 'Sunken Defector' on the bottom of your deck.
72657.flavorText: "I've got a sinking feeling about this evil Queen."

72336.name: Azsharan Gardens
72336.text: Give all minions in your hand +1/+1. Put a 'Sunken Gardens' on the bottom of your deck.
72336.flavorText: That's not what I meant when I asked you to water the garden.

72926.name: Azsharan Mooncatcher
72926.text: Divine Shield. Battlecry: Put a 'Sunken Mooncatcher' on the bottom of your deck.
72926.flavorText: The light of Elune faded from the ruins of Zin-Azshari, but not its treasures.

77374.name: Azsharan Ritual
77374.text: Silence a minion and summon a copy of it. Put a 'Sunken Ritual' on the bottom of your deck.
77374.flavorText: The harmonious silence surrounding the ritual was unceremoniously BROKEN when HAROLD began eating stale potato chips.

72896.name: Azsharan Saber
72896.text: Rush. Deathrattle: Put a 'Sunken Saber' on the bottom of your deck.
72896.flavorText: Even in ancient times, the Night Elves were committed cat people.

72254.name: Azsharan Scavenger
72254.text: Battlecry: Put a 'Sunken Scavenger' on the bottom of your deck.
72254.flavorText: Some local Murloc populations have adapted to survive in the harsh conditions of the ruins, much to the fascination of Sir Finley.

77209.name: Azsharan Scroll
77209.text: Discover a Fire, Frost or Nature spell. Put a 'Sunken Scroll' on the bottom of your deck.
77209.flavorText: Kids these days are always scrolling on their tomes.

72212.name: Azsharan Sentinel
72212.text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Put a 'Sunken Sentinel' on the bottom of your deck.
72212.flavorText: For some, the Sundering was the collapse of civilization. For others, it was a great core workout.

77016.name: Azsharan Sweeper
77016.text: Battlecry: Put a 'Sunken Sweeper' on the bottom of your deck.
77016.flavorText: The enchanted objects of Zin-Azshari have extremely long warranties.

72113.name: Azsharan Trident
72113.text: Deathrattle: Put a 'Sunken Trident' on the bottom of your deck.
72113.flavorText: Nevermind the barnacles! A well-crafted weapon is eternally useful.

72111.name: Azsharan Vessel
72111.text: Summon two 3/3 Pirates with Stealth. Put a 'Sunken Vessel' on the bottom of your deck.
72111.flavorText: Not even the sturdiest Highborne ship could survive the churning waters of the Sundering.

71701.name: Baba Naga
71701.text: Battlecry: If you've cast a spell while holding this, deal 3 damage.
71701.flavorText: A folktale told to Naga children to scare them from swimming too close to the surface.

71705.name: Barbaric Sorceress
71705.text: Taunt. Battlecry: Swap the Cost of a random spell in each player's hand.
71705.flavorText: Her four arms are for casting, and her forearms are for crushing.

71709.name: Barbed Nets
71709.text: Deal 2 damage to an enemy. If you played a Naga while holding this, choose a second target.

72316.name: Bioluminescence
72316.flavorText: The perfect card for Spell Damage Shaman and Spelling Bee Shaman.

72120.name: Blackscale Brute
72120.text: Taunt. Battlecry: If you have a weapon equipped, summon a 5/6 Naga with Rush.
72120.flavorText: Black, the scales of angry Naga! Red, the flames of Azshari's past!

72488.name: Blackwater Behemoth
72488.flavorText: What's a Blackwater Behemoth's favorite meal? Fish n' Ships.

72007.name: Blademaster Okani
72007.text: Battlecry: Secretly choose to Counter the next minion or spell your opponent plays while this is alive.
72007.flavorText: Yet ANOTHER sword fighter that spams counters.

72473.name: Blood in the Water
72473.text: Deal 3 damage to an enemy. Summon a 5/5 Shark with Rush.
72473.flavorText: Fish are friends, not food! Gilgoblins on the other hand…

76926.name: Bloodscent Vilefin
76926.text: Battlecry: Dredge. If it's a Murloc, change its Cost to Health instead of Mana.
76926.flavorText: Tired of eating Jellyfish and Peanut Butter fish, it’s moved on to more gruesome meals.

72117.name: Bone Glaive
72117.flavorText: Resourceful Demon Hunters find a use for every part of the Demon.

72480.name: Bootstrap Sunkeneer
72480.text: Combo: Put an enemy minion on the bottom of your opponent's deck.
72480.flavorText: Part of the deck, part of the crew.

73466.name: Bottomfeeder
73466.text: Deathrattle: Add a Bottomfeeder to the bottom of your deck with permanent +2/+2.
73466.flavorText: Someone keeps adding fish to my deck, and I'm going to get to the bottom of it.

73428.name: Bubblebot
73428.text: Battlecry: Give your other Mechs Divine Shield and Taunt.

71646.name: Bubbler
71646.text: After this minion takes exactly one damage, destroy it. (Pop!)

73443.name: Chum Bucket
73443.text: Give all Murlocs in your hand +1/+1. Repeat for each Murloc you control.
73443.flavorText: Time to go in for the krill.

75633.name: Clash of the Colossals
75633.text: Add a random Colossal minion to both players' hands. Yours costs (2) less.
75633.flavorText: Don’t let this distract you from the fact that in 1998, Ozumat threw Neptulon off Shell in a Cell, and plummeted 16 fathoms through an announcer’s table.

72417.name: Click-Clocker
72417.text: Divine Shield. Battlecry: Give a random Mech in your hand +1/+1.

75589.name: Clownfish
75589.text: Battlecry: Your next two Murlocs cost (2) less.
75589.flavorText: His jokes are hilarious if you know Nerglish.

85810.name: Coilfang Constrictor
85810.text: Battlecry: Look at 3 cards in your opponent's hand and choose one. It can't be played next turn.
85810.flavorText: How do you know when someone has a crush on you? They take your breath away.

71921.name: Coilskar Commander
71921.text: Taunt. Battlecry: If you've cast three spells while holding this, summon two copies of this. ( left!) (Ready!)
71921.flavorText: Then thou shalt count to three, no more, no less. Three shall be the number thou shalt count, and the number of the counting shall be three. Four shalt thou not count, neither count thou two, excepting that thou then proceed to three. Five is right out.

71712.name: Colaque
71712.flavorText: Ten thousand years ago, the city of Zin-Azshari fell to the bottom of the sea... and partially onto Colaque's shell.

77609.name: Commander Sivara
77609.text: Battlecry: If you've cast three spells while holding this, add those spells back to your hand. ( left!) (Ready!)
77609.flavorText: With six legs, gills, and an impressive array of magic, Sivara is an all-terrain-spellcaster.

75639.name: Commander Ulthok
75639.text: Battlecry: Your opponent's cards cost Health instead of Mana next turn.
75639.flavorText: He likes to spend his free time in his garden, growing Bloodradish, Bloodcabbage, and his favorite, Bloodbloom.

74884.name: Conch's Call
74884.text: Draw a Naga and a spell.

72973.name: Coral Keeper
72973.text: Battlecry: Summon a 3/3 Elemental for each spell school you've cast this game.
72973.flavorText: This here is Carl. They're in charge of these elementals. Not all of them get along, so sometimes Carl corrals the quarreling coral.

72536.name: Crabatoa
72536.flavorText: This giant crab loves to sink entire naval fleets, but it'll settle for a single dinghy in a pinch.

71940.name: Crushclaw Enforcer
71940.text: Battlecry: If you've cast a spell while holding this, draw a Naga.

77208.name: Cutlass Courier
77208.text: After your hero attacks, draw a Pirate.
77208.flavorText: It may be a cutlass, but you can cut lads with it too.

74988.name: Disarming Elemental
74988.text: Battlecry: Dredge for your opponent. Set its Cost to (6).
74988.flavorText: "You can have these back when you learn to play nice."

73712.name: Dozing Kelpkeeper
73712.text: Rush. Starts Dormant. After you've cast 5 Mana worth of spells, awaken.
73712.flavorText: *Yaaaaawn* wake me up in another 5 Mana.

73442.name: Dragged Below
73442.text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Give your opponent an Abyssal Curse.
73442.flavorText: I know this is a frustrating situation you’re in, Captain, but there’s no need to curse.

80120.name: Drown
80120.text: Put an enemy minion on the bottom of your deck.
80120.flavorText: If you play it on a Naga, they drown in their sorrows instead.

72340.name: Emergency Maneuvers
72340.text: Secret: When a friendly minion dies, summon a copy of it. It's Dormant for 1 turn.

72109.name: Excavation Specialist
72109.flavorText: With the jungles of Un’goro mapped out and the ruins of Uldum fully uncovered, explorers have to go a little out of their depth in their search of the great unknown.

74890.name: Filletfighter
74890.flavorText: "What do you mean this isn't the meal you asked for? ! I made you a Fillet Minion!"

73462.name: Flipper Friends
73462.text: Choose One - Summon a 6/6 Orca with Taunt; or six 1/1 Otters with Rush.
73462.flavorText: Despite the harsh conditions, friends can still be found under the sea.

72587.name: Forged in Flame
72587.text: Destroy your weapon, then draw cards equal to its Attack.
72587.flavorText: Don't worry, your wounds are self-cauterizing!

75072.name: Fossil Fanatic
75072.text: After your hero attacks, draw a Fel spell.

72588.name: From the Depths
72588.text: Reduce the Cost of the bottom five cards in your deck by (3), then Dredge.
72588.flavorText: "This is why I'm afraid of the deep end of the pool."

80117.name: Front Lines
80117.text: Summon a minion from each player's deck. Repeat until either side of the battlefield is full.
80117.flavorText: With the line in the sand crossed, the battle for the Throne of Tides had begun.

71841.name: Gaia, the Techtonic
71841.text: Colossal +2 After a friendly Mech attacks, deal 1 damage to all enemies.
71841.flavorText: Always planning ahead, Ini knew she'd need this invention to protect all her other inventions.

72929.name: Gifts of Azshara
72929.text: Draw a card. If you played a Naga while holding this, do it again.
72929.flavorText: Barber: What do you want? Naga: You ever have a thirst for arcane power? Barber: Say no more.

74741.name: Gigafin
74741.text: Colossal +1. Battlecry: Devour all enemy minions. Deathrattle: Spit them back out.
74741.flavorText: How much storage does Gigafin's Maw have? About a giga bite.

71919.name: Glaiveshark
71919.text: Battlecry: If your hero attacked this turn, deal 2 damage to all enemies.
71919.flavorText: Can smell a drop of vengeance in the water up to a mile away.

72553.name: Glugg the Gulper
72553.text: Colossal +3 After a friendly minion dies, gain its original stats.
72553.flavorText: Food can be scarce in the Abyssal Depths, leading its top predators to pursue any potential source of sustenance. Even extra crunchy ones.

72119.name: Gone Fishin'
72119.flavorText: Rogues want me Fish fear me

72021.name: Gorloc Ravager
72021.flavorText: Be careful what you fish for.

73465.name: Green-Thumb Gardener
73465.text: Battlecry: Refresh empty Mana Crystals equal to the Cost of the highest Cost spell in your hand.
73465.flavorText: Sometimes all a plant needs is, like, A LOT of water.

72590.name: Guard the City
72590.text: Gain 3 Armor. Summon a 2/3 Naga with Taunt.
72590.flavorText: At thousands of feet below the surface, it's a pretty high-pressure job.

72484.name: Handmaiden
72484.text: Battlecry: If you've cast three spells while holding this, draw 3 cards. ( left!) (Ready!)
72484.flavorText: Why did she unspool the last roll of royal toilet paper?!

74755.name: Harpoon Gun
74755.text: After your hero attacks, Dredge. If it's a Beast, reduce its Cost by (2).

73713.name: Hedra the Heretic
73713.text: Battlecry: For each spell you've cast while holding this, summon a minion of that spell's Cost.
73713.flavorText: Hedra was cast out millennia ago for her divisive opinions among the Naga, such as "Turning into evil underwater serpent people was bad, actually."

73799.name: Helmet Hermit
73799.flavorText: I’d avoid asking if it wants to join the battle. It’s been pretty crabby lately.

75552.name: Herald of Chaos
75552.text: Lifesteal Battlecry: If you've cast a Fel spell while holding this, gain Rush.
75552.flavorText: They used to be called the Heralds of Order before all of this silly Sundering nonsense.

76583.name: Herald of Light
76583.text: Battlecry: If you've cast a Holy spell while holding this, restore 6 Health to all friendly characters.
76583.flavorText: Wake up! No sleeping in with the fishes!

75560.name: Herald of Nature
75560.text: Battlecry: If you've cast a Nature spell while holding this, give your other minions +1/+1.
75560.flavorText: A mother of plants in mother of pearl.

73445.name: Herald of Shadows
73445.text: Battlecry: If you've cast a Shadow spell while holding this, steal 2 Health from a minion.

73424.name: Holy Maki Roll
73424.flavorText: If you use all 10 mana, that's called the 'Lunch Special.'

72935.name: Hydralodon
72935.flavorText: Deep beneath the waves, this hydra grew to incredible size based on a steady diet of literally anything that crossed its path.

75631.name: Igneous Lavagorger
75631.text: Taunt Battlecry: Dredge. Gain Armor equal to its Cost.
75631.flavorText: Lava shark, doo doo doo doo doo doo.

72482.name: Illuminate
72482.text: Dredge. If it's a spell, reduce its Cost by (3).
72482.flavorText: BEHOLD THE GLORY OF A NEW CUP!

75637.name: Immolate
75637.text: Light every card in the opponent's hand on fire. In 3 turns, any still in hand are destroyed!
75637.flavorText: "Well if you cared about those cards so much, why didn't you play them?"

80112.name: Immortalized in Stone
80112.flavorText: They all secretly have 'Deathrattle: Become very mortalized.'

73068.name: Ini Stormcoil
73068.text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly Mech. Summon a copy of it with Rush, Windfury, and Divine Shield.
73068.flavorText: Before setting her sights on exploration, Ini was known for many inventions, such as the airborne breadmaking dirigible, the hypersprocket 200X zoom binoculars, and jobes (jean robes).

76261.name: Inkveil Ambusher
76261.flavorText: You’ve got it wrong. She releases ink when you’re scared.

80121.name: Jackpot!
80121.text: Add two random spells from other classes that cost (5) or more to your hand.
80121.flavorText: Find someone who looks at you the way Hooktusk looks at loot.

76223.name: K9-0tron
76223.text: Battlecry: Dredge. If it's a 1-Cost minion, summon it.
76223.flavorText: You merely adopted the Battlegrounds. I was born in it. Molded by it.

78113.name: Kotori Lightblade
78113.text: After you cast a Holy spell on this, cast it again on another friendly minion.

72594.name: Lady Ashvane
72594.text: Battlecry: Give all weapons in your hand, deck, and battlefield +1/+1.
72594.flavorText: This is your brain on Azerite.

72024.name: Lady Naz'jar
72024.text: While in your hand, this transforms after you cast a Fire, Frost, or Arcane spell.

73723.name: Lady S'theno
73723.text: Immune while attacking. After you cast a spell, attack the lowest Health enemy.
73723.flavorText: Only a S'theno deals in absolutes.

76258.name: Lightray
76258.text: Taunt Costs (1) less for each Paladin card you've played this game.
76258.flavorText: Lightrays, much like rays of light, tend to be seen closer to the surface.

72649.name: Mecha-Shark
72649.text: After you summon a Mech, deal 3 damage randomly split among all enemies.
72649.flavorText: "Why didn't you just build a normal submarine. Only you can fit inside" "WhY DiDn'T YoU JuSt BuIlD anormalsub-WHY DO YOU THINK WREZIG!! If you can build a freaking Mecha-Shark, then you build a freaking Mecha-Shark!"

73471.name: Miracle Growth
73471.text: Draw 3 cards. Summon a Plant with Taunt and stats equal to your hand size.
73471.flavorText: I’ve got NO idea what’s in that fertilizer.

76117.name: Moonbeam
76117.text: Deal 1 damage to an enemy, twice.
76117.flavorText: The light of the moon may have disappeared from Zin-Azshari after the Sundering, but not its power.

71694.name: Multi-Strike
71694.text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. They may attack an additional enemy minion.
71694.flavorText: “I said you get two attack, not two attacks!”

71917.name: Murkwater Scribe
71917.text: Battlecry: The next spell you play costs (1) less.
71917.flavorText: The pen is mightier than the trident.

73427.name: Myrmidon
73427.text: After you cast a spell on this minion, draw a card.
73427.flavorText: He didn't have time to Myrmidon the other half of his armor before combat started.

71949.name: Naga Giant
71949.text: Costs (1) less for each Mana you've spent on spells this game.
71949.flavorText: He might be giant, but he’s still a couple thousand protein shakes away from competing in the Colossal Wrestling Championship.

72928.name: Naga's Pride
72928.text: Summon two 2/2 Lionfish. If you played a Naga while holding this, give them +1/+1.
72928.flavorText: Lionfish, Naga, and Spears, oh my!

71688.name: Naval Mine
71688.text: Deathrattle: Deal 4 damage to the enemy hero.
71688.flavorText: A Naval Mine? I'd rather it be Naval Yours.

74894.name: Nellie, the Great Thresher
74894.flavorText: Not to be mistaken for her freshwater cousin, Nessie, this massive creature was harnessed to carry Hooktusk's favorite ship.

75583.name: Neptulon the Tidehunter
75583.text: Colossal +2, Rush, Windfury Whenever Neptulon attacks, if you control any Hands, they attack instead.
75583.flavorText: Neptulon, tired of filling hands, is now throwing hands.

72592.name: Obsidiansmith
72592.text: Battlecry: Dredge. If it's a minion or a weapon, give it +1/+1.
72592.flavorText: Was able to produce more effective weapons than his predecessor, Kelpsmith.

75580.name: Ozumat
75580.text: Colossal +6 Deathrattle: For each of Ozumat's Tentacles, destroy a random enemy minion.

72938.name: Pelican Diver
72938.flavorText: The pelican’s beak is so big, some Colossal minions can even fit inside!* *This is a lie.

72418.name: Piranha Poacher
72418.text: At the end of your turn, add a 1/1 Piranha Swarmer to your hand.
72418.flavorText: This snack certainly isn’t smiling back…

72509.name: Piranha Swarmer
72509.text: Rush After you summon a Piranha Swarmer, gain +1 Attack.
72509.flavorText: One Fish, Two Fish. Less Fish? You wish.

72495.name: Pirate Admiral Hooktusk
72495.text: Battlecry: If you've summoned 7 other Pirates this game, plunder the enemy! ( left!) (Ready!)

75556.name: Polymorph: Jellyfish
75556.text: Transform a minion into a 4/1 Jellyfish with Spell Damage +2.
75556.flavorText: While Ini’s first use of the Spontaneous Gelatin Transmalgamizer may have gotten her banned from the Gnomish Cooking Convention, she’s never one to throw away a new invention.

72984.name: Predation
72984.text: Deal 2 damage. Costs (0) if you played a Naga while holding this.
72984.flavorText: No need to worry! The squid is actually being sent to a nice kelp farm upstate.

71945.name: Priestess Valishj
71945.text: Battlecry: Refresh an empty Mana Crystal for each spell you've cast this turn. ( )
71945.flavorText: Some of the more stoic priestesses worry that she's living too lavishjly.

71690.name: Pufferfist
71690.text: After your hero attacks, deal 1 damage to all enemies.
71690.flavorText: "...and then I'll hit 'em with the ol' puffercut!"

72923.name: Queen Azshara
72923.text: Battlecry: If you've cast three spells while holding this, choose an Ancient Relic. ( left!) (Ready!)
72923.flavorText: Hobbies include: Ordering subjects around, making deals with old gods, and taking long walks under the beach.

72485.name: Queensguard
72485.text: Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each spell you've cast this turn.
72485.flavorText: Archnemesis of the Guardian of Kings.

76250.name: Radar Detector
76250.text: Scan the bottom 5 cards of your deck. Draw any Mechs found this way, then shuffle your deck.
76250.flavorText: "Yup! I definitely don't know how to read radar."

72423.name: Radiance of Azshara
72423.text: Fire Spell Damage +2 Your Nature spells cost (1) less. After you cast a Frost spell, gain 3 Armor.
72423.flavorText: Uses Arcane, Fire, and Frost magic to vanquish Queen Azshara's foes. And for her skincare routine!

72648.name: Rainbow Glowscale
72648.flavorText: She prefers saying that she has Arcane, Fel, Fire, Frost, Holy, Nature, and Shadow Spell Damage +1.

74886.name: Raj Naz'jan
74886.text: After you cast a spell, deal damage equal to its Cost to the enemy Hero.
74886.flavorText: When you play the Coin, he deals emotional damage.

72586.name: Reefwalker
72586.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Piranha Swarmer.
72586.flavorText: A gentle giant with some not-so-gentle friends.

72320.name: Rock Bottom
72320.text: Summon a 1/1 Murloc, then Dredge. If it's also a Murloc, summon one more.

72508.name: Scalding Geyser
72508.flavorText: ”Wow, what’s that land formation called?” “It s’cald a Geyser.”

72598.name: School Teacher
72598.text: Battlecry: Add a 1/1 Nagaling to your hand. Discover a spell that costs (3) or less to teach it.
72598.flavorText: She also tutors 3 Piranha Swarmers on her off hours.

72416.name: Schooling
72416.text: Add three 1/1 Piranha Swarmers to your hand.
72416.flavorText: A group of Piranha are known as a Scholomance.

72650.name: Seafloor Gateway
72650.text: Draw a Mech. Reduce the Cost of Mechs in your hand by (1).

77018.name: Seafloor Savior
77018.text: Battlecry: Dredge. If it's a minion, give it this minion's Attack and Health.
77018.flavorText: "TURTLE PROCURED. ADMINISTRATING BANDAGES AND KISSES. BOO BOO MUST BE ELIMINATED."

72932.name: Seascout Operator
72932.text: Battlecry: If you control a Mech, summon two 2/1 Mechafish.
72932.flavorText: The Mechafish are actually totally autonomous. We gave her a fake control pad, as a joke.

73464.name: Seaweed Strike
73464.text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. If you played a Naga while holding this, also give your hero +4 Attack this turn.
73464.flavorText: Even as mechs, fish will still end up wrapped in seaweed.

72338.name: Security Automaton
72338.text: After you summon a Mech, gain +1/+1.
72338.flavorText: Honestly, I feel less secure when it's around.

72504.name: Selfish Shellfish
72504.flavorText: Keeps any ancient book it finds all to its shelf.

72487.name: Serpent Wig
72487.text: Give a minion +1/+2. If you played a Naga while holding this, add a Serpent Wig to your hand.
72487.flavorText: Legends say that all those who look into her eyes are turned to plush.

76259.name: Shattershambler
76259.text: Battlecry: Your next Deathrattle minion costs (1) less, but immediately dies when played.
76259.flavorText: Someone didn’t realize the ‘cold, black heart’ thing was supposed to be a metaphor.

76225.name: Shellshot
76225.text: Deal 3 damage to a random enemy minion. Repeat this with 1 less damage.

73431.name: Shimmering Sunfish
73431.text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Holy Spell, gain Taunt and Divine Shield.
73431.flavorText: Just keep shimmering, just keep shimmering.

71781.name: Sir Finley, Sea Guide
71781.text: Battlecry: Swap your hand with the bottom of your deck.
71781.flavorText: "No need to worry, ol' chums, I have the map right here. It says to continue going straight down!"

73436.name: Sira'kess Cultist
73436.text: Battlecry: Give your opponent an Abyssal Curse.
73436.flavorText: "Sira'kess, she's the best! Puts her followers to the test.

71729.name: Slimescale Diver
71729.flavorText: You try putting on a wetsuit with scales.

73792.name: Slithering Deathscale
73792.text: Battlecry: If you've cast three spells while holding this, deal 3 damage to all enemies. ( left!) (Ready!)
73792.flavorText: Colossal minions know her better as Slithering Damagescale.

72333.name: Smothering Starfish
72333.flavorText: Is a sucker for small talk.
